"```sql\nSELECT \n    (SUM(CASE WHEN YEAR(loan.date) = 1997 THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END) - \n     SUM(CASE WHEN YEAR(loan.date) = 1996 THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END)) / \n    NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN YEAR(loan.date) = 1996 THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END), 0) * 100 AS growth_rate\nFROM \n    loan\nJOIN \n    account ON loan.account_id = account.account_id\nJOIN \n    disp ON account.account_id = disp.account_id\nJOIN \n    client ON disp.client_id = client.client_id\nWHERE \n    client.gender = 'M';\n``` \n\nThis SQL query calculates the growth rate of the total amount of loans for male clients between the years 1996 and 1997. It sums the loan amounts for each year and computes the growth rate based on the provided formula. The `NULLIF` function is used to avoid division by zero in case the sum for 1996 is zero."